1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new chapter to title 12.1 of the North Dakota Century
2 Code, relating to surveillance and animal harassment with a robot; and to provide a penalty.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new chapter to title 12.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
5 enacted as follows:
6 Definitions.
7 As used in this chapter:
8 1. "Harass" means engaging in behavior that annoys, threatens, or intimidates an animal,
9 causing a change in behavior due to stress or perceived harm.
10 2. "Livestock" includes beef cattle, dairy cattle, sheep, swine, poultry, horses, bison, elk,
11 fur animals raised for their pelts, and any other animals that are raised, fed, or
12 produced as a part of farming or ranching activities.
13 3. "Robot" means an artificial object or system that senses, processes, and acts using
14 technology, including the associated elements, communication links, and artificial
15 intelligence. The term includes remotely piloted aircraft.
16 Surveillance by robot - Penalty.
17 1. An individual may not use a robot to:
18 a. Conduct surveillance of another individual, a residence occupied by another
19 individual, or any private real property, whether owned or rented.
20 b. Photograph another individual under circumstances in which that individual has a
21 reasonable expectation of privacy.
22 2. This section does not apply to:
